<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Manchester City are 'hopeful' striker Sergio Aguero will be fit for their season opener against Wolves after making a fast recovery from knee surgery just three months ago.</p>

<p>The star frontman was expected to miss the start of the 2020-21 campaign after going under the knife in late June.</p>

<p>But according to the Sun, the Argentine will be available for selection by Pep Guardiola in the September 21 clash after making quick progression in his rehabilitation.</p>

<p>Manchester City are hopeful Sergio Aguero will be available for their season opener vs Wolves</p>

<p>Pep Guardiola may be able to select the striker after initial fears he would miss start of season</p>

<p>The report claims Aguero is now pain free and his mobility is improving which has given City confidence he will be available to feature in the Molineux face-off.</p>

<p>The north-west club will be thankful their season kicks off a week later than most teams after they and Manchester United were granted extra time off due to their European exploits last season.</p>

<p>Their season came to an end only three weeks ago when they were eliminated from the Champions League at the quarter-final stage after a 3-1 defeat against Lyon.</p>

<p>Aguero was absent for the disappointing defeat and Guardiola will be hoping he can keep the 32-year-old fit for as much of the season as he can.</p>

<p>The prolific Argentine has reportedly made swift recovery after knee surgery in late June</p>

<p>The prolific forward scored 23 times in just 32 appearances last season and is the club's all-time highest goalscorer.with a staggering 254 goals.</p>

<p>City will be desperate to wrestle their Premier League crown back off Liverpool this campaign after finishing 18 points behind the Reds in the last campaign.</p>
